Dragonfly is a &quot;Password-Authenticated Key Exchange&quot; protocol (or=
<br>
&quot;PAKE&quot;). =A0Dragonfly was proposed to CFRG 2 years ago [PROPOSAL]=
.<br>
Compared to better-known PAKEs, Dragonfly has no security proof, a<br>
lack of extensive security analysis, nonfunctional complications added<br>
for IPR reasons, and some security issues [REVIEW].<br>
